acModularGateway.name: acModularGateway
acModularGateway.contactinfo: Postal: AudioCodes LTD 4 Horesh Road Yehud 56470, ISRAEL Tel: 972-3-5394000 Email: support@audiocodes.com
acModularGateway.description: This MIB is solely for AudioCodes modular Gateways. Use this MIBs status section for cross reference tables connecting analog/digital ports to the modules on which they are. The MIB has become deprecated as of version 5.2. It will be obsolete as of version 5.4

acModularGWModuleTable.name: acModularGWModuleTable
acModularGWModuleTable.description: This table holds the information about each module in Audiocodes' modular gateways. If an index (Module number) is shown - then the module is in and working. You can also see the modules type, number of ports and it's first port's logical number allowing you to calculate which port is which logical trunk or analog channel. (This information is also obtainable in the acModularGWTrunkTable and acModularGWChannelTable).

acModularGWModuleIndex.name: acModularGWModuleIndex
acModularGWModuleIndex.description: Module index. 1 is the first Module - top left corner. 2 is the next Module to the right and so on. 4 is under 1.

acModularGWModuleType.name: acModularGWModuleType
acModularGWModuleType.description: Module Type. The Modules are characterized according to their ports. 0 = Digital - Quad. 1 = Analog - FXS. 2 = Analog - FXO. 4 = Digital - FALC.

acModularGWModuleNumOfPorts.name: acModularGWModuleNumOfPorts
acModularGWModuleNumOfPorts.description: The number of physical interfaces in a module, analog or digital.

acModularGWModuleFirstPortNum.name: acModularGWModuleFirstPortNum
acModularGWModuleFirstPortNum.description: The logical number as seen in the general trunk/analog-channel table of the first port in the module in question. Since analog and digital ports can be operational at once, analog and digital ports may have same logical number.

acModularGWTrunkTable.name: acModularGWTrunkTable
acModularGWTrunkTable.description: This table shows the trunk location and type.

acModularGWTrunkIndex.name: acModularGWTrunkIndex
acModularGWTrunkIndex.description: Trunk index. The trunk in question's logical number.

acModularGWTrunkOnModuleNum.name: acModularGWTrunkOnModuleNum
acModularGWTrunkOnModuleNum.description: Module number on which the trunk in question is placed. 1 is the first Module - top left corner. 2 is the next Module to the right and so on. 4 is under 1.

acModularGWTrunkOnPortNum.name: acModularGWTrunkOnPortNum
acModularGWTrunkOnPortNum.description: Physical Port on module. 1 - left most port.

acModularGWAnalogPortTable.name: acModularGWAnalogPortTable
acModularGWAnalogPortTable.description: This table shows the analog port location and type.

acModularGWAnalogPortIndex.name: acModularGWAnalogPortIndex
acModularGWAnalogPortIndex.description: Channel index. The channel in question's logical number.

acModularGWAnalogPortOnModuleNum.name: acModularGWAnalogPortOnModuleNum
acModularGWAnalogPortOnModuleNum.description: Module number on which the analog port in question is placed. 1 is the first Module - top left corner. 2 is the next Module to the right and so on. 4 is under 1.

acModularGWAnalogPortOnPortNum.name: acModularGWAnalogPortOnPortNum
acModularGWAnalogPortOnPortNum.description: Physical port on module. 1 - left most port.
